From the root folder run this command to run it: 
python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload


app/
├── core/
│   ├── config.py              # Loads environment variables and app settings
│   ├── cors.py                # CORS middleware setup
│   └── rate_limit.py          # Request rate limiter (anti-spam)
│   └── security.py      # Anti Scrapping Middleware

│
├── models/
│   └── schemas.py             # Pydantic models for request/response
│
├── routers/
│   └── chat_router.py         # Chat endpoints (/chat and /stream)
│
├── services/
│   ├── openai_service.py      # Handles OpenAI API requests (sync + stream)
│   ├── pinecone_service.py    # Initializes Pinecone index client
│   └── rag_service.py         # RAG: retrieves & builds contextual knowledge
│
├── utils/
│   └── contact_utils.py       # Detects contact queries, quick FES contact responses
│
└── main.py                    # FastAPI entry point
└── requirements.txt           
└── .example.env               # example env


## ⚙️ Features

### ✅ Chat Endpoints

* `/chat`: Standard JSON chat response.
* `/stream`: Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming for live token responses.

### 🧠 RAG Integration

* Retrieves relevant context from Pinecone vector database.
* Passes context to OpenAI model for enriched, context-aware replies.

### 🛡️ Security & Limits

* **Rate limiting** (via `slowapi`) prevents abuse / DDoS-style flooding.
* **Anti-scraping middleware** blocks bot-like User-Agents.
* **CORS restrictions** for controlled access origins.


### 🧱 Modular Design

All major features (rate limiting, CORS, RAG, OpenAI, Pinecone, etc.) are isolated in reusable components.
